<HEADLINE>
<P>
THE INTIMATE EXPERIMENT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Is pursuing one's own "needs" more important than "subjecting our children to 
an experiment" in child care that may fail? 
</P>
<P>
What choices do these middle- to upper-class moms have? Working part time, job 
sharing, working in the home, altering (lowering) one's life style are all 
viable considerations. There are so many homes that "look so much like the 
American dream" filled with children being raised by strangers. 
</P>
<P>
MARILYN PASSWATER 
</P>
<P>
Redlands 
</P>
