<HEADLINE>
<P>
TAXES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
As I write my check to the IRS, I'm reflecting on the bills it will pay to keep 
our country going. I feel good about contributing to education, housing, health 
care, and saving the environment. But that just adds up to 14 cents of my tax 
dollar. My hair stands straight on end when I think about 52 cents of that 
dollar going into military budgets. Wouldn't we, in the end, be a stronger and 
better nation if we could turn those figures around? 
</P>
<P>
JUNE BEHRENS 
</P>
<P>
Rancho Palos Verdes 
