<HEADLINE>
<P>
LEIMERT LIVING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
I appreciated the article about Leimert Park (At Home, April 2). 
</P>
<P>
According to your statistics, I am one of the 3.7% white residents of Leimert. 
I moved into the neighborhood very recently after having lived in apartments in 
Santa Monica, Westwood and West Hollywood. I now own my own home. 
</P>
<P>
A typical two-bedroom house in Leimert Park currently goes for about $160,000. 
For this type of money, there is no place in Los Angeles with the mix of 
convenience, location, neighborhood pride and simple straightforward beauty 
like Leimert. I can think of many neighborhoods on the Westside with far more 
graffiti. 
</P>
<P>
I invite Angelenos who have never been to this part of town to educate 
themselves. Come to Leimert for a Sunday drive and also check out the new 
shopping center and beautiful adjacent hillside neighborhoods of View Park and 
Windsor Hills. I guarantee a surprise. 
</P>
<P>
RANDALL E. ADAMS 
</P>
<P>
Los Angeles 
</P>
</TEXT>
