</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The problem with the white, mainstream rock generation is intolerance toward 
other tastes in music, particularly when that genre happens to be dominated by 
artists who are not white. 
</P>
<P>
It is futile to believe that rap, reggae or any other form that differs in any 
way from the mainstream will not suffer the same fate as disco. The sad fact of 
American life still is intolerance and racism, in the music industry and 
elsewhere. 
</P>
<P>
CHRIS ELLIS 
</P>
<P>
San Bernardino 
</P>
