<HEADLINE>
<P>
GRADING SULLIVAN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Sullivan gives Shakespeare in L.A. Theater a "D" but mentions ony the Taper, 
Old Globe, Ahmanson and L.A.T.C. Has he seen the Bard's work at any waiver 
theaters recently? 
</P>
<P>
With talented and versatile actors working in our theaters -- albeit on the 
small-theater level -- we don't need a Brit to show us how to do Shakespeare. 
What we do need is a critic who grades the work of all the students, not just 
the big kids in the class! 
</P>
<P>
STANLEY BENTON 
</P>
<P>
Los Angeles 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Letter to the Editor 
</P>
</TYPE>
