TROOPER IS GUNNED DOWN OVER UNPAID TRAFFIC TICKET 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
TERRA ALTA, W. Va. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A state trooper serving an arrest warrant for an unpaid traffic ticket was shot 
to death Saturday by the violator, who was then killed, officials said. 
</P>
<P>
Ercil Layton, 62, fired at Trooper J. T. Brammer and his partner after they 
entered his house to serve the warrant for three missed appearances in traffic 
court, police said. 
</P>
<P>
Brammer, 42, was killed and his partner, R. J. Hicks, 35, was wounded in the 
arm, officials said. It was not immediately clear whether the troopers returned 
fire or whether Layton shot himself. 
