</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Track and field athletes from Ivy League rivals Harvard and Yale joined forces 
to defeat a combined team from English universities Oxford and Cambridge in the 
rain at New Haven, Conn. 
</P>
<P>
The U.S. team defeated the British, 21-13, in the 32nd trans-Atlantic meet, a 
traditional event that has featured such legendary track and field athletes as 
Roger Bannister, the first man to run the mile faster than four minutes. 
</P>
<P>
The meet also was scored as a dual meet between Harvard and Yale, which the 
Crimson won, 88-75, as freshman sprinter Derrick Horner won the 100 and 200 
meters, placed second in the long jump and anchored Harvard's winning 400-meter 
relay team. 
</P>
</TEXT>
