<HEADLINE>
<P>
NEWSWIRE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Dominic Olejniczak, former president of the Green Bay Packers Corp. and a 
former Green Bay mayor, died Saturday morning at his home. 
</P>
<P>
Olejniczak's death was stroke-related, a relative said. 
</P>
<P>
Olejniczak, 80, was president of the National Football League for 24 years and 
spent 10 years as the city's mayor. 
</P>
<P>
He became president of the Packers on April 28, 1958, when the team was 
struggling. The Packers had not had a winning record in 10 years and had just 
finished their worst season ever with a 1-10 record. 
</P>
<P>
Olejniczak headed the search committee that brought Vince Lombardi to Green Bay 
as coach and general manager, which launched the most successful era in the 
team's history. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Column; Obituary 
</P>
</TYPE>
<SUBJECT>
<P>
TEAM OWNERS; GREEN BAY PACKERS (FOOTBALL TEAM); COACHES 
</P>
</SUBJECT>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA041689-0188 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 44974 </DOCID>
<DATE>
<P>
April 16, 1989, Sunday, Home Edition 
</P>
</DATE>
