<P>
POLICE PERSUADE BEATING SUSPECT TO SURRENDER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Cypress police and a man they suspected of beating his wife negotiated for 6 
hours before the man came out of his house and surrendered early Saturday 
morning, police said. 
</P>
<P>
The suspect, Kevin William Yearout, 20, of Cypress, was jailed on suspicion of 
assault, police said. His bail was set at $10,000. 
</P>
<P>
Police were summoned after Yearout's wife ran to a neighbor's house a little 
after 11 p.m. Friday. She told officers that Yearout had "numerous weapons" in 
the house. 
</P>
<P>
It took police until about 5 a.m. to persuade Yearout to surrender. Officers 
said they searched the house and found no weapons. 
</P>
<P>
Yearout's wife was treated for minor injuries, police said. 
