<HEADLINE>
<P>
SCHOOL CREATES MEMORIAL ART SCHOLARSHIP FUND 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By CATHY CURTIS 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
In memory of Megan Hart Jones, who attended the Art Institute of Southern 
California when it was known as the Laguna Beach School of Art, the school has 
established a scholarship fund. Contributions will be used to provide studio 
art scholarship awards for bachelor of fine arts students pursuing degrees in 
painting, drawing, sculpture or photography. 
</P>
<P>
Individuals who contribute $250 to the fund will receive a small etching by 
Jones, either "English Sheep" -- tiny sheep scattered on a field sloping down 
from a panoramic landscape -- or "Flowers and Shells" in which the subjects are 
scattered within an abstract grid format. Those who contribute $25 or more will 
receive the tiny, privately printed booklet "Portrait of a Story" in which 
Jones writes with humor and passion about the experience of creating her major 
work, "Eternal Force." 
</P>
<P>
Checks can be made payable to AISC -- Megan Hart Jones Scholarship Fund, and 
sent to the Art Institute, 2222 Laguna Canyon Road, Laguna Beach, Calif. 92651. 
For information, call (714) 497-3309. CATHY CURTIS 
</P>
</TEXT>
<GRAPHIC>
<P>
Photo, Megan Hart Jones feeds birds in Hyde Park, London, 1985. A scholarship 
fund has been set up in her memory. 
</P>
</GRAPHIC>
